2 AASSIGN~
#Immortal Building BuildingSetup~
#END~
Syntax: aassign <filename>.are  Example:  aassign edo.are
 
AASSIGN temporarily assigns all rooms, objects, and mobiles in the area
range to your pfile.  This allows you to use rlist, olist, mlist, and
reset list.  This also means that typing savearea, reset area, or 
instazone will affect this area.  
 
To save changes permenantly, type "aassign none" and foldarea.
 
&rWarning&w!! Do not have an area aassigned to yourself when getting personal
vnums assigned to you.  The personal vnums will overwrite the area file.
 
In order to assign a proto area to yourself, you must either have that
area bestowed to you by a Greater God or higher.
 
In order to assign a nonproto area to yourself, you must either have
that area bestowed to you by an Exalted+. Even if you have the area bestowed
only Lesser+ can aassign themselves nonproto areas.
~

2 'ACCOUNT' 'ACCOUNTS'~
#General~
#END~
Syntax:  accounts online
Syntax:  accounts <account>
Syntax:  accounts <account> editing off
Syntax:  accounts <account> changes <value>
Syntax:  accounts <account> disconnect
Syntax:  accounts <account> name <name> <password>
Syntax:  accounts <account> password <password>
Syntax:  accounts <account> email <email>
Syntax:  accounts <account> ban <ban|allow>
Syntax:  accounts <account> release <player> <password>
Syntax:  accounts <account> delete <player>
Syntax:  accounts <account> reloadplayers [account name]

Accounts is the primary command to modify and fix account
problems online.  Lets go over the arguments provided.

online        - Shows who is online
<accounts>    - With no argument it simply shows account and its values.
editing off   - Removes the editing status from an account.
changes       - Adjusts how many changes an account has done in an hour.
                The default is only to allow 15 an hour (HELP CSET)
disconnect    - Forces the account to disconnect (along with the players)
name          - Changes the name of the account, must supply a password too.  The
                name and password you provide become the new ones
password      - Changes the password of the account
email         - Changes the email address of the account
ban           - Toggles the ban on the account
release       - Releases the player from the account, password is used to retrieve
                it later if wanted (or for another account to pick it up)
delete        - Deletes a player from the account.  Will try to delete the pfile if
                it exists, but will atleast remove the name from the player list.
reloadplayers - Reloads the account from file.  It removes the old data and
                inserts the new data on every player online belonging to that
                account.  Does not need to logoff the player to do so.     
~

