1 AGGRESSION INSULT~
#General~
#END~
Syntax:  insult [target]

The aggression system is something that was introduced pre 2.1.  This allows
for a better group experience and thus different tactics for defeating the
enemies.  Every time you land a blow against an enemy, cast a spell that
hurts the enemy, or heal yourself or an ally, a value is assigned that
and it adds aggression toward you.  The target will attack you if you
are the highest on the aggression meter.

The order of most to least aggression follows

   Healing the tank
   Healing Other (see intelligence check below)
   Casting while not the tank
   Casting as the tank (see intellience check below)
   Landing an attack not as the tank
   Landing an attack as the tank
   Insult (depends on damage landed and intelligence check)

As noted, the more intelligent the target is, the less aggression is assigned
on the scenerios listed above.  In some cases, it can drop it down the list if
the target is extremely intelligent.

As before, using a high percentage blocking shield will make the target move off
of you.  If you are using a shield, you suffer an aggression decrease on landed 
blows and a slow reduction over time (in battle).  The better the the chance of
a shield block, the more increase you will see in the over time reduction.

Note:  There is a command called insults that is a nonskill version for RP.

----Continued in AGGRESSION2----
~

1 AGGRESSION2~
#General~
#END~
Next, a quick not about healing.  Healing is a very nasty aggression stealer that
can be used to keep it and also to get killed.  Anytime you heal someone (take
this as a hint, they have to be in a group to get this affect) you will get
aggression from all enemies that are fighting your group.  So if you have 3
enemies on Player A and 3 on Player B.  If you heal Player A you will get
on the aggression list of all 6 enemies.  Do this enough and you will become
the target.  It comes in handy here to be able to have a tank offer up some
heals of their own and perhaps have a second healer that can carry in some
healing in the background.  The same would go with group healing spells, expect
nearly instant aggression if you have a lot of members in your group.

Lastly, the insult skill.  This can come in handy for pure melee classes and
any other class that wishes to tank.  It uses 2 rounds (1 second) and attempts
to insult the target.  You always offer out an insult, but you never really
know if it lands.  If the target is unintelligent, the insult will almost always
land if you have any expertise in the skill, but on highly intelligent enemies
it has a reduced affect all the way to no affect.

Note:  This system does not work on players of course, insult is useless on players
and will not work.  Kingdom mobs still will not allow a buffer attack.  This is where
you purchase a bunch of cheap units to "pinch" away at the other forces.  In the past
as is the same now, the military units will target unequiped foes first and dispatch
them quickly.  Regular mobs still use intelligence checks to aim at different body
parts, but will no longer care about stances now (aggressive = more damage equals
more aggression, etc).
~

