0 DEATH~
#General Information~
#Combat~
#END~
When your character dies, you are reincarnated in the newbie camp or at
the recall spot of your Kingdom's choicing.  Your corpse is left behind
where you were killed, together with all of your equipment.  Your gold
stays with you (mysterious is it not?).

Any spells which were affecting you are cancelled by death and your
constitution is lowered slightly. Following/groups are not affected by death.

Corpses decay after time.  When this happens the objects inside a corpse
will be dumped to the room it is in.  The objects last till a reboot or a
crash happens.  The corpse itself will not decay for 2 whole days so you
have plenty of time to go get your corpse.  If you cannot get your corpse
through normal means there is drag (HELP drag) and the spell summon corpse
(HELP SUMMON CORPSE).  Also, anyone who is grouped with you can drag your
corpse or loot it for you.

Lastly, the morgue (HELP MORGUE) was introduced shortly after the death changes.
You can use the morgue to retrieve your corpse.  If you die in a quest, you can
use QPS to get your corpse back.  If you die anywhere else it will either cost you
5 HP if you are have under 100 hp or it will cost you 5% of your hp if you are over
100 hp.  You have to wait 15 MINUTES if you are over 100 hp before you can pull
back your corpse.  All of this is done at the morgue (HELP MAP).
~

1 DEATHBLOW CRIT 'CRITICAL HIT' 'DEATH BLOW'~
#General~
#END~
A deathblow is when a hit is good enough to kill the enemy no matter
how much life is left.  Deathblows can happen anywhere, but more likely
to happen to head shots and specially neck shots.  You can increase you
chance of a deathblow by using a stabbing attack.

