1 HARVEST~
#Kingdoms Management~
#END~
Harvest time is very important in Rafermand because you need food to feed
your people, and not having any food for a full game year could be absoultely
devistating to a kingdom.  So, it is very important to understand how this
harvest system works and what is the best avenue of approach.

To start off, there are only 2 kinds of foods in Rafermand at this moment:
corn and grain.  Corn and grain both grow at a different time, the times
are the following

      Corn -  April - July (Game Time) (Help TIME INFO for Conversions)
      Grain - June - September (Game Time)
      
During the following times, any planted grain or corn fields will start to
increase from 0 to the max of 6000.  Even if you plant a corn field in May,
it will also start to increase till July.  After the end of the last month
of growth, the amount of resources will drop from whatever the amount there
is now to 0.  It takes about 1.5 game months go go from 6000 to 0, and this
is a flat reduction (so .75 months for 3000 to 0).  Growth is not flat, and
it depends on how many resources you already have.

So what does this all really mean?  Here are some tips.

1.  Always plant atleast twice as many fields as you need food for just in
    case you have to harvest one month early or late.  The more you plant, the
    more time you have to harvest
2.  Try to plant both kinds of food and attempt to harvest them.  
3.  Purchase silos if you need to store extra food.  All that food is going to
    do no good if you don't have somewhere to put it.
4.  It is typically a good time to start extracting anywhere from the last month
    of growth to 15 days after the last month.  Ex for Corn: July 1 - August 15
5.  Talk with other kingdoms, they might be interested in a trading agreement for
    your extra food or would be willing to sell you food for something else like
    coins, wood, or stone.
~

