7 LAW LOOTING~
#General~
#END~
This is not really a law, but more of a guideline for looting when
a group is fighting a multi-player fight.  Often poor looting guidelines
are set and this can be used as a good start.

A command called roll was put into the game to aid in this process.  With
this command players can roll a value from 1 to 100 and the game will spit
out a number.  You can use this to decide who wins the prize, or prizes.
Typically, the standard is the highest roll wins.  If there is a tie the
people who tied roll again till there is a clear winner.

In case of multiple loot, you roll on each item and the winner of 1 item is
not capable of winning any more loot unless the loot is large than the party
(there are 5 items and 4 people).  You can pass on any item at any time and
even go back if needed.  If everyone passes on an item twice, it is free for
the taking by any individual in the group without a roll.

Lastly, if you already possess the said item (on any character in your account)
you should pass on the item in favor of someone who does not have the item.  In
addition, if you are in a group with clear roles, you should pass on any item that
does not benefit the character you are playing at the time of the looting.
~

1 'LAW LOOTING'~
#General~
#END~
There is no clearly defined rule for looting and this really is not
a rule to follow, but more of a general guideline for looting in
multi-player groups.  If you cannot think of your own format to follow
it might be easiest to use this guideline so any question of looting
can be addressed and straightened out

First, the roll command was introduced a few months back.  The main purpose
of this command was for deciding on who should loot.  It can be used to roll
a 1d100 dice (or any other set of numbers, 1-100 is the default).  The value
range the target choose along with the result will be displayed for everyone
in the room to see (for this reason you should not rely on someone to tell
you what the result was if they died, everyone should be in the room so there
is no argueing).  The winner of the roll wins the item in quest.  Read below
for more detailed scenerios.

If more than one item is involved, everyone rolls on the items in quest, only
change is once you won an item you cannot roll on another item UNLESS there are
more items than party members (5 items and 3 party members).  Any member of the
party can pass on any item if they want.  Only 2 rounds should go by, if the
whole party passes on 1 object twice, the object is up for free loot from anyone
in the party.  Once everyone has won an item, everyone can then roll on the items
in question.  It is a good idea to roll on the items everyone wants first to get
those out of the way.

Lastly, if your character or any character in your account already owns the item
you are rolling on, you should pass on an attempt to roll for an item.  If this
holds true for everyone, then everyone can roll on the item.  Also, if your party
is setup into certain roles, you should pass on an item that does not help with
your roll.  If you are the tank that doesn't cast, rolling on a high mana object
should be passed on in favor of those who can use it.  If everyone passes on an
object for this reason then anyone that can use it can roll on it.  This rule is
probably the most confusing and "arguementive" of all of them, it might be a good
idea to drop it if you are having problems deciding.

NOTE:  A party member consists of anyone "actively" present during a kill.  This
includes anyone that has died and is not currently in the area, has been there for
till the end rather it is tanking, healing, rezing, etc.  If a person goes LD they
have 5 minutes to get back on or they forfeit their chance at an item.  Anyone can
pick up said items as long as you know they are not NODROP/NOGIVE and hold on to them
till the winner is decided.  Once this format is setup, it is not up to anyone to
change it or decide *hay I don't like Player X so he/she does not get the item*.  If
things are going to be fair, let the dice decide the winner.
~

