1 LEARN~
#Skills~
#General Information~
#END~
&w&GSyntax: learn <mobile> [skill/group] [mastery]

This is the main command that allows you to learn a new skill or spell.  In order to do
this you must find a trainer.  A trainer is easy to spot because they have &w&W[TRAINER]&w&G
before their names.  Once you find a trainer, you may type this:

  learn <mobile name>
  
This will give you a listing of all that this trainer teaches.  Once you do this, there are
a few things you have to take into consideration before you can learn from this trainer.

1.  In order to learn beginner, you need to meet the requirements of that Tier (HELP TIER).  Tier
    1 requires nothing, but Tier 2-4 requires you have skills/spells in the Tier below the one you
    are trying to learn at a certain mastery.  To learn what Tier 2-4 require, type 
    listgroups toadvance <group> (HELP LISTGROUPS).  For starting out, you can only learn Tier 1
    spells or skills.  You can find out what ones are available by typing &c&wlistgroups allgroups&w&G to
    find a group and then using &c&wlistgroups <group>&w&G to look at the skills/spells in that group.
    The ones that are &w&YYellow&w&G are Tier 1 spells/skills (HELP TIER for what the colors mean).
  
2.  There will be a monitary requirement to learn.  Cost is based on the mastery of the skill/spell you
    are trying to learn (HELP MASTERY) and any taxes applied by the kingdom.
    
3.  In order to advance to Novice you need 4 points in the skill/spell.  Expert needs 7 and Master needs 10.

4.  If you are learning Beginner and it is a spell, you will need a spellbook.  You can go find a spellbook
    mob and use sbook to purcahse the book (HELP SBOOK)
    
Once you have learned the skill/spell you wanted, you will be able to get better at it by using it.  All
skills/spells increase in power as you use it more often.  You can see your strength of skills/spells by
using the &c&wskills&w&G command (HELP SKILLSCOMMAND).

&w&CSEE ALSO:  &w&WSKILLS  LISTGROUPS  TIER  MASTERY  SBOOK  SKILLSCOMMAND
~

