1 'LEVEL' 'LEVELS' 'CLASS' 'CLASSES'~
#General Information~
#END~
&c&wRafermand simply doesn't have levels or classes, instead a unique advancement system is used. 
Character achievement is completely up to you, the player, there is no level or class restriction 
regarding the use of spells, skills or equipment.  You can pick any skill or spell your soul desires, 
but there are restrictions to how far you can go with it (HELP SKILLS).  Some skills and spells 
affect each other, which means, advancing in a certain spell could result in losing some efficiency 
in another spell or skill.

In a sentence, your abilities increase when you use them, and decrease when you dont.

This simple rule applies to every aspect of character achievement, for example:
* Fighting and getting damage will slowly build up your hitpoints.
* Casting spells will build up your mana as well as your intelligence.
* Movement is improved by the new Endurance ability, the higher your endurance, the less moves it 
  take you to move around.

To find out how well you are doing in all these aspects, use the gscore command (HELP GSCORE) to see 
abilities and stats progression, and the skills command (HELP SKILLS) to see spell and skill
progression.

&CSEE ALSO:  &G&WGSCORE    SKILLS    STATS
~

