1 LISTGROUPS~
#Skills~
#END~
Syntax: listgroups allgroups
Syntax: listgroups <group name>
Syntax: listgroups <skill name>
Syntax: listgroups toadvance <group name>

Listgroups is the main command used to find out what skills/spells are available to you.  Since there are
no classes in Rafermand, all the spells/skills that are available are seen with this command.  It is possible
to be able to use everything listed in listgroups, but the system is setup so you can only really dominate in
a few areas, or be average in a handful.

listgroups allgroups will show you all of the available groups and what sphere they belong to.  A sphere is
one of the main "sections" of skills.  AS of this helpfile there is Warrior, Thief, Hand-to-Hand, Cleric, and
Mage.  Each one of these spheres has a few groups in them.  Each one of the groups has a few skills or spells
available that you can learn at trainers (HELP LEARN).  For more info over spheres and the dirty functions of
the skill system, check out (HELP SPHERES) but be ready for a rather detailed reading

listgroups <group name> will give you a listing of skills and spells available in each group.  You will notice
there are colors for each skill/spell.  This reflects what tier this spell/skill belongs to (HELP TIER).  You will
also notice the color, this is also explained in (HELP TIER).

listgroups <skill name> will allow you to find out what Sphere/Group a skill/spell belongs to.

listgroups toadvance <groupname> is used to tell what is required to learn spells/skills in a certain Tier.  In
order to learn Tier2 spells/skills, you will need so many Tier1 spells/skills at Novice.  This will give you
all this information along with how many you need.  It is very important to understand the Tier system if you
plan on having access to the more advance skills/spells in Rafermand.

&w&CSEE ALSO:  &w&Wlearn skills skillrules mastery tier spheres
~

