0 MAGIC~
#Magic~
#END~
The magic system here in Rafermand goes along with our unique skill system.  It
is important to understand each Group in the two Magical Spheres of Cleric and
Mage.  The 6 groups are as follows : fire, air, water, earth, energy, divine.  In
each group, you have 4 tiers of spells.  The 1st tier being the weakest and the 4th
tier being the strongest magic known to Rafermand (help tier).  Along with the tiers,
each group has certain strengths and weaknesses.  Below is some info about 
the spells in each group.

Fire -   One of the more physically powerful groups.  Fire in the mage set is used to damage
         equipment with its steady heat and attack small to large groups of foes with destructive
         spells such as Fireball.  When it comes to resisting Fire spells, there is a 1/2 damage
         save against the attack spells.  When it comes to the cleric side, Fire is used mainly
         in such spells as animate dead, group healing magic of fortify, and the ever popular 
         protection of sanctuary.
       
Earth -  Another good physical group.  Earth has the ability to bring great damage if used for
         its destructive measures.  On the flip side, the protective side of Earth offers some of
         the best protections by ways of armor, shield, and stone skin.  Along with that, Earth
         boasts one of the most powerful Mage spells in the game, Antimagic Shell.  A very
         powerful spell that helps to reduce the effectiveness of magic against the target. On the
         other side of the group there is the helpful healing spells of cure poison and blindness.
         In addition, those Clerics who master this group have access to one of the most destructive
         Clerical spells in the game, sacred blast.  Those who wish to use this group faces 1/4 of
         damage if a save is made, but can damage equipment
        
-------Continued in MAGIC2-------   
~

1 'MAGIC BANE'~
#Magic Mage Offensive~
#END~
A very powerful spell by the affect it can have on a character by one who has mastered its
use.  Magic bane places a magical curse on the subject making it a lot easier to land spells
for their full affects on the target.  Unlike curse, magic bane cannot be revoked by a remove
curse spell.  Those who are masters of this spell find it much easier to inflict damage on
the target with their spells
~

0 MAGIC2~
#Magic~
#END~
Air   -  Another useful group, and the most powerful on one level.  Air offers a lot of unique spells
         that aren't available anywhere else.  Such spells as wizardeye, uplift, and know enemy are
         of huge benefit to any adventurer who wants to make his/her name known in the world.  In
         addition, there are the benefits of summon and portal, which can be used to travel around
         the world in a rapid fashion.  The attack spells in the Air group are the most powerful in
         all of Rafermand, but they suffer a negate (no damage) save.  This means it is either full
         power or miss with such spells
        
Water -  A rather balanced group to choose.  Water is essential toward living in the world, and some
         of the spells offered in this group are essential to survival too.  Starting off early with
         a simple spell like create spring can come in handy when there is a lack of water to drink.
         In addition, the Cleric side of Water offers the 3 basic healing spells, which come in handy
         to the beginning adventurer when it comes to restoring health on the fly.  In addition to that,
         there is the offering of breathing underwater with aquabreath, the ability to see far away
         distances with farsight, and the ever powerful unravel defense.  Saves versus spells in this
         sphere cause 1/2 damage
        
Energy - A very powerful group on a handful of different levels.  Mages and Clerics alike who have mastered
         this group are respected and feared alike because of their power to do many different things.  Energy
         is the most difficult group to Master, but the payoff for dedication is quite evidant to the Experts
         and the Masters.  Energy is the only group that contain spells that can drain health from the target
         and give it to the caster.  The spells are a little weaker than their counterparts in the other groups,
         but they contain this hidden strength.  In addition, the clerics of this group have access to the
         damage spells available to clerics.  Lastly, there are the rather beneficial spells of enchant weapon,
         true sight, pass door, recharge, knock, and weaken.  On top of that, Energy contains one of the most
         sought after spells in all of Rafermand, sanctify.  Besides the draining spells, there are straight
         damage spells in Energy and all these spells including the draining ones are 3/4 damage if saved
         against, so they offer the most damage if saved against.
         
Divine - A cleric only group.  Divine contains some of the core spells essential to any cleric.  Ranging from
         bless, harm, and heal up to the most powerful healing spell in Rafermand, power heal.  Divine is harder
         to learn than any other group, but the payoffs are good in the short list of great spells available to
         the cleric.

