4 MAKEKEEPER~
#Immortal Building BuildingMobs~
#END~
Making a special shopkeeper for a player involves a few things, and it is
VERY IMPORTANT you understand how it works so you don't create any bugs
or crashes because the mob isn't setup right.  Here is a list of what
is needed to be done.

1.  Use makekeeper command on the person of choice.
2.  The room and the mob MUST have the same VNUM to work correctly.
3.  The mob needs to be non prototype and have the CASTEMOB flag on it, and if
    told by another immortal, the pacifist flag.
4.  Need to use the shopmake/shopset to create a normal shop for the
    keeper.
5.  Need to instaroom and foldarea the mob.  Make sure the mob IS NOT prototype
    and it HAS the castemob flag on it.
6.  Tell the player to type keeperstat and resetkeeper to make sure the commands
    are working ok.
7.  Inform them to read all the helpfiles over the keeper commands.  Also inform
    them the buy0 - buy2 and level0 - level1 will not work till they are ALL set
    to something besides 0.
8.  Remind them they can transfer gold using goldtake and goldgive
9.  Tell them they cannot give items to the mob, but have to sell it to them.
    Remind them this does not cost them or the mob anything.
10. After that tell them to resetkeeper and explain to them to use it after doing
    a money transfer or doing a keeperset
11. Make a note at 9003 and don't EVER switch into the keeper.

That is the process in a nutshell.  You can view the helpfile KEEPERWORK for
more info on how exactly this all works.

&G&WSEE ALSO: &YKEEPERSET KEEPERSTAT GOLDGIVE GOLDTAKE KEEPERINFO KEEPERWORK
         PCSHOPS KEEPEROWN           
~

