3 MAPEDIT~
#Wilderness~
#END~
Usage: mapedit sector <sector number>
Usage: mapedit save <mapname>
Usage: mapedit exit <vnum>
Usage: mapedit exit map <mapname> <X> <Y>

Mapedit is used to modify values on the Overland (Wilderness).  The two main
commands used to do this is mapedit and mapat (HELP MAPAT).  Mapedit is
used to do it 1 coordinate by 1 coordinate.  Mapat is used to do it in lines.
There is also the blockmove command (HELP BLOCKMOVE), but it is only used
in rare situations where you need to literally copy a block of an area to
another area.

Mapedit is also used to create exits to an area.  The proper way to create
an exit is as such.

1.  Find the spot you want to exit to be on the wilderness.  Next type this
       mapedit exit <vnum>
2.  Go into the exit to the area.  Then type this
       redit exit <dir> 16000
       redit exflags <dir> overland
       redit excoord <dir> <x> <y>

