1 MAPFIGHTS~
#Wilderness~
#END~
While roaming around on the wilderness, you will eventually be attacked by
something.  General rule of thumb is the more people you have grouped with
you, the better you are off.  Once your party gets so big though, more mobs
will start to come for you, so that can be either a good or bad thing depending
on what you want.

In addition, if you are in unsafe areas (such as not on the road), more mobs
will be loaded.  In general, the more moves it takes to move in that sector, the
more dangerious that sector is for loading mobs.  It is possible to load 4 to 5
times more mobs in certain sectors than others, so be careful.

Once you are in a fight, the only way to really get away is to run away from the
mobiles enough that they stop chasing you or flee into an area.

&YSEE ALSO: &G&WWILDERNESS WIZARDEYE ASCIICHARACTER MOVEREQUIREMENTS
          MOUNT LOOKAROUND MOUNTDEATH
~

2 MAPLINE~
#General~
#END~
Syntax:  mapline <dir> <start> <end> <new sector> <till sector> [skips]
   dir:  0 - North, 1 - East, 2 - South, 3 - West
   
Used to fill out a map, particularly after you outline it (such as a new
continent).  You choose the direction you want the fill to happen and you
choose the start and end value (so if you are going east you are going
to provide the north most cooridnate and the south most coordinate).  Then
you provide the sector you want to fill in, then you provide the sector
at which to stop at.  The skips is optional but you can actually skip the
till sector any number of times (default is 0).  

The main use as mentioned is outlining.  You perhaps create a shoreline for
the continent then you sit at the very north side of the continent and you
provide the west most coodinate then the south most coordinate.  Then you
provide the new sector (say field) then provide the till sector (shoreline
since that is your outline).  It will then run south and fill till it finds
that shoreline.
~

