1 MORAL MORALE~
#Kingdoms~
#END~
Morale is a value that ranges from 1-103 and it is represented in your townvalues screen
Every month, you go up for consideration for a Moral Increase/Decrease/Nochange.  Once
you reach a certain moral, you will either increase or decreate in size.  The values
are such.

Size 1 = 1           Size 2 = 6         Size 3 = 12
Size 4 = 18          Size 5 = 24        Size 6 = 30
Size 7 = 42          Size 8 = 54        Size 9 = 72        Size 10 = 100

You advance to the above sizes by reaching the moral value listed, you decrease in size by
reaching the value below the ones listed.  Moral gain/decrease has a few factors, they are
as followed.

1.  Double Consumption.  This is turned on by default, they consume twice as much of the
    resources as they need, this increase moral.
2.  Taxes.  The higher the taxes, the less moral, the lower the taxes, the default tax for
    a town ranges from 6 to 9 percent.  Leaving it at 7.5 is a fairly safe bet.  You can
    only increase taxes once every Game Year (Kingdom or Town)
3.  Number of Units in service.  If your town size (HELP TOWNSIZE) is 4 or greater, if you
    go over a certain number your moral chance will lower.
    
The chance to gain is a -100 to 100 roll and it starts at 0.  Double Consumption gets you
positive gains, Lower Taxes gets you positive gains.  If you meet Double Consumption on
all resoures, you will gain a moral point unless taxes or units is decreasing your chance.
Not have enough food to meet Single Consumption is an automatic reduction of moral and
not meeting the other resources will drop your chance down quite a bit.  

Lastly, you can change from No/Single/Double consumption on Food/Lumber/Stone/Coins with

the townvalues command (HELP TOWNVALUES).  You can change these at any time.
~

1 MORGUE~
#General~
#END~
