1 MOUNTS~
#Wilderness Mounts~
#END~
It is now possible to buy mounts that act like pets and will save when you
save and quit when you quit.  In addition, just like pets they will follow
you and you can order them.  Also, one of the new and cool features of the
new mount system is that you can now improve certain mounts.  The mount will
slowly gain more endurance over time, just like players do.  More endurance
in a mount means they can move farther and carry your huge amounts of equipment
with them at the same time.

There are a few tips for people with mounts.
* If you lose your mount, recall, it will show back up at recall.
* Don't use area attacks like fireball or earthquake.
* If you have a mount, try to use full names of mobs you want to attack
* You can restore movement to your mount with mountfood
* It is possible to trade mounts at certain unknown shops.
* If a mount dies it loses endurance (HELP MOUNTDEATH)
* There are special mounts out there that are better in battle, magically
  blessed, and even can fly!

&w&YSEE ALSO: &w&WMOUNT FOOD    NOURISH    STABLES    MOUNTDEATH    SETFREE
~

1 MOVEMENT MOVE 'MOVE SYSTEM' ENDURANCE~
#General Movement~
#END~
Move is the the point value that is used for movement.  Move always stays at a flat 1000
points, but it is affected by 2 other things, Endurance and Weight.  Endurance is a point
value that is used to measure how far you can move without becoming winded.  You start
to get winded once your move value reaches 500.  Higher endurace will make it longer to
get to 500.  In addition, if you are carrying a lot of weight in the form of inventory
or on your body in the form of armor and weapons, it will also make it easier to
get winded.

Before you get winded there are two levels, above and below 800.  Below 800
causes you to suffer a bit of movement lag (nothing like below 500) and
above 800 causes no lag.  (NOTE:  These movement lag rules do not apply to
someone who is mounted)

Once you reach 500 points, you will start to get messages about breathing increasing and
it will become harder to move and longer (lag).  If you reach around 75 points, you will
pass out and enter a stun like state for a few seconds.   It is always a good idea not to
go below 200 points.

If you are looking to travel far distances, it is a good idea to stick to roads (HELP WILDRNESS)
or even better, go purchase a mount (HELP MOUNTS).

In addition, you will also get tired while in battle, certain commands require a lot of
energy to use, and mana requires a lot as you start to build up toward the higher level
spells, so it is a good idea even for a mage to stay well shaped.

What Increases Endurance
-------------------------------------------------
* Moving around (Won't gain endurance while on a mount)
* Battle

What Decreases Endurace
-------------------------------------------------
* Time
* Death

NOTE:  See (HELP MOVEMENTCOMMAND) for help over the command

&CSEE ALSO:    STATS    GSCORE    WILDERNESS    MOUNTS
~

