#END~
Each sector you go into requires a certain amount of movement to move
into.  The movement is either subtracted from you or the mob you are
mounted on.  In the wilderness, movement is about 5 to 7 times more
than the normal requirements while in the city, so it is important to
carry mount food or have your mount full of movement.  Also, it is
important to save movement by moving down sectors like roads or path
that require a lot less movement than something like hills or forest.

To get a list of sectortypes and the degree of movement it required to
move into the sector, use the showascii command.

