1 MXP~
#General Information~
#General Newbie~
#END~
This mud features the use of the mud protocal called mxp. What does this 
mean, well here is a brief description and why I want to support it. 

Mxp is a markup-language, much like xml and html. It allows me to put in 
tags like you see in html and add in some custom tags like you can in xml. 
This also allows me to create links and all you need to do is right click 
on an object/mob/word to get a list of actions you can perform. This means 
you do not even need to know the syntax, you just right click on it, get a 
list of options, and then choose the one you want to use. This makes things 
more newbie friendly, and can enhance the play experience for all. 

There are other features of mxp that can be used, but that is one the 
primary reasons to use it. If you want to play around with mxp, this is 
what you need.... 

Mushclient - www.mushclient.com (get the most recent version)
Zmud - www.zuggsoft.com (Need z6.22 BETA or higher)

Both of these clients are Win32 (windows 9x, NT, 2000, etc). There is no 
linux client out there or mac, and I do not suppose there will be one any 
time soon. In addition, it is important to get the latest version of either 
of these clients because the protocal is still in its infancy and is being 
developed more and more. So to get the most out of the features, you need 
the newest client. If you are a cheapskate and cannot afford the $25 US, 
you can always use Mushclient forever without paying a dime (even though 
you can register it) 

NOTE:  There is an mxp command used to turn on/off some functionality.  The
helpfile is (HELP MXPCOMMAND)
~

1 MXPCOMMAND~
#General~
#END~
Syntax:  mxp mapwindow [on/off]
Syntax:  mxp mapwindow [close/open]

Mxp is the command used to turn on/off certain parts of the mxp protocol used
in Rafermand.  Due to the limited amount of clients that can use mxp, mxp
functions are turned off by default.  You can use this command to enable certain
functions and others are done automatically depending on what client you
are using.  The following commands are available atm:

mapwindow (Zmud 6.62+ only) - Used to send the output of the wilderness map
to a window.  This will popup the window for you and turn on the function for
you.  Once on, the map data will be sent to the window for you.  It will
also resize itself when needed, this resizing will cause the window to return
to its default position of upper-right hand corner.  Things that cause a resize
are enhancements/dehancements of sight like darkness and wizardeye.  The map
is also opened/closed when needed (like entering/leaving the map).  The
following options are available: 

   on - Turns it on and loads up the map
   off - Turns it off and removes the map
   close - Simply closes the map
   open - Simply opens the map
~

