0 OGRE~
#General Information Races~
#END~
----------------------------------------------BIO----------------------------------------------------
Ogres, creatures of nearly unsurpassed size and ferocity, the ogres and demi-ogres (Some ogres have 
been able to crossbreed with other "monstrous" races within Rafermand, though the ogres tend to 
share basically the same characteristics as eachother.) tend to be a reclusive people.  They populate 
harsh lands, being able to cultivate crops that only a race so crude could sustain themselves off of.  
It is said of the ogres that they can grow anything in even the harshest of climates due to an odd, 
innate sense of nature, but they have grown accostomed (maybe even to the point of enjoying) things 
that would be the bane of other civilizations.  Ogres are highly shamanistic, using primal, natural 
energies as a primitive form of invocation, which further drives their colonies out of general 
acceptance.  Ogres have few outside relations with the other races unless they are on a personal basis 
(such as ogre mercenaries, quite an asset), or when tools have broken and have to be 'replaced', at 
the cost of any nearby colonies of other races. (note, ogres have only the most brutish of capabilities
in their shamanistic powers...only a VERY RARE ogre will be able to tap into the natural forces for 
anything more than cultivating the crops the species lives off of.  One of the few tools created by the
ogres, specialized weaponry wrought from the twisted plants grown by their villages serve as deadly 
weaponry, sought after by those with strength and skill enough to use them properly.  Also, rare
clans of ogres are known to be less nomadic, though only one 'city' of such is rumoured to exist in the 
isles wrapped eternally in shadow...
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Additional Information

* Exceptional Strength/Contitution
* Greatly reduced Dexterity
* Exceptionally reduced Intelligence and Wisdom
* Lowered Agility
* Innate defense against physical damage
* Innate weakness to magic
* Innate strength against fire/cold
* Innate hinderence in learning magic
* Increased hp building (gains new hp quicker than all other races)
~

