of the one attacking, and the one being attacked having parry turned on, and the
weapon you are using.  If you use identify or an identify scroll on a weapon you
should see the following

   Parry Mod 20  Parry Block Mod 2

Parry Mod is the actual value you use to parry with.  The higher the parry mod the
better the weapon is at parrying.  The Parry Block Mod is used to block a parry
with.  The value of 2 is very poor.  The following weapon sets are listed below
and their strength at the two catagories

   Swords - High Parry Rate, Average Block Rate.  Rapier is the best parrying sword
   Axes - Slightly Lower Parry Rate than Swords, Good Block Rate.
   Polearms - Average Parry and Block Rate
   Daggers - Best Parry Rate, Low Block Rate.  Main Gauche is the best parrying weapon
   Staves - Slightly better than Polearms in both areas
   Blunt - Low Parry Rate, Best Block Rate.

Custom weapons can have different rates depending on the type of the weapon and
what it is meant for, so always identify custom weapons.  Ore will not affect
the parry rate of a weapon, a copper dagger will be just as affective as a steel
one at parry.

Lastly, there is a 1 second lag (2 rounds) if you don't have the parry skill.  You
get a round nocked off at Novice and Expert.
