1 PIGGYBACK~
#General~
#END~
Syntax:  piggyback <target>

Piggyback allows you to jump on the back of a player and hitch a ride.  Whenever
the player giving the ride moves, the other one on his/her back will move along
too.  This works a lot like mount but there are a few key differences.  Mainly
you don't control the person you are riding, the person giving the ride is in
control.  Also, you cannot fight while riding someone.  If a fight starts with
either party involved, the riding status is immediately broken.  However, magic
can be casted while riding.  Any teleportation magic (astral, word of recall) will
affect both parties (including if the rider casts).  

Another thing with piggybacking is fighting is now allowed and any damage dealt
to either party will immediately brake the union.  If the rider wants to stop
the ride all that is needed is dismount.  In order to get the rider off the one
giving the ride, the toss command needs to be used (HELP TOSS).  Also, chance
cannot be changed by either party, only way to sit or sleep is to get rid of the
rider or to stop riding. 

Next, all moving costs are attributed to the person giving the ride.  The
weight of the rider is added to the total weight of the one giving the ride.
The weight is the actual weight of the rider (as shown by examine) along with
equipment weight (shown in score).  If that weight is too much, then piggyback
will fail.  If the weight is enough, the weight cost will affect movement
cost and a penality of double movement cost will be assigned no matter what.

On a final note, piggyback status is broken if either party leaves the game.
If a copyover happens the piggyback status is saved for that copyover only.
If a crash/reboot happens the status is reset.

NOTE:  Only immortals can stop this from happening by setting the noriders flag
in config.  Players cannot stop this from happening but it is considerable an
aggressive act to jump on someone's back when not invited, so be warned.
~

