There are a few rules to know about when it comes to player killing.
Those are.

1.  Camping will NOT BE TOLLERATED.  This is sitting in front of an
entrance with the intent to kill ALL who enter.  This will be one of
the few matters dealt with by immortals, and it will be dealt with
a harsh punishment.

2.  Banking will NOT BE TOLLERATED.  This applies to nonpkill areas
and it included making an area unrunable.  This includes such acts
as forcing keys not to pop, ruining mobprogs which are crutial to the
area, and charming mobs and leaving.  For more info type help banking.

3.  Weapons no longer disarm to the ground, but to the inventory of
everyone in any type of circumstance.  This rule might be changed
later if we feel it is needed.

4.  We do tollerate more bickering and "name calling" in FPK and APK
zones than we do in the normal parts of the game, but you should try
to avoid crossing the line into extreme harrassments, threatening in
an RL matter, sexual comments, and other talk/actions that are not
appropriate anywhere.  Most actions will get a warning based on the
intensity of the comment, after that, you will not be warned again.

5.  If you are being bullied by a player, it is up to the other players
to help you out.  Our system is setup not to reward such conduct, but
some players simply love to kill players who are weaker.  Try
talking to some of the outstanding players for help with the issue.

6.  Any items lossed or damaged during PKILL rather it is NPK, APK,
or FPK will not be reimbursed.  Neither will any "potential" items
on a FPK corpse that might of been lossed to a crash or other
incident.

7.  Finding loopholes without the EXPLICIT permission of immortals in
the SPK areas will not be allowed.  If you find one by accident, you
are to report it IMMEDIATELY or face punishment.

8.  There are hardcoded rules to prevent clan members from attacking
eachother, and this will not be changed.  Kingdom members cannot
attack eachother in the Kingdom Map/Kingdom cities, but can in the
normal areas and normal wilderness. There will be hardcoded rules to prevent
people from PKing a person while they are fighting, but until then PKing someone
while they are fighting a mob is HIGHLY illegal, so don't do it.

9.  You are not allowed to outcast a player from a clan simply to "setup"
that individual and kill him/her in a loot area.  This will not be tolerated
and will be punished.  If you are going to outcast a player, both players
must be in a safe area.

10. You cannot camp in the respawn room of player's kingdom and kill him/her.
This is called multikilling and is not allowed.  First there will be a warning, and
after that slayings, freezing, banning, whatever it takes.
~

