1 PORTALS~
#Magic~
#END~
In Rafermand (Code FeAr v1.0) the introduction of new portal systems was
put into place.  Portal systems are actual portal areas located in the
city you belong to and the portals out in the Wilderness.

In order to find these portals, you first must start out by going to the
portal in your city and using the command 'huntportals' to start to hunt
portals or end hunting portals.  Once you are hunting portals, you cannot
use or be targeted by spells that would allow you to move around like
astral or summoned by summon.  You will have to locate the portals in
the map.  To make it a little more fun, the portals will now show up till
you are close to them, but the portals are close to major areas in the map
so just search around to find them.  (Please note, you will not find portals
you haven't found already or be able to mark new ones if you are not hunting
portals.)

Once you find a portal, you just goto the square it is on and use the command
'markportal' to add it to your list.  Once you have found the portal, you can
use 'listportals' to get a list of all the portals you have found.  Also, once
you have marked the portal, it will show up on the map in normal view so you
can go to it easier and use it.

Once you have decided to stop hunting new portals, you can go back and use the
'huntportals' command again to stop hunting the portals so you can use them to
portal, astral, etc.  Once you get to a portal you want to use, you can use the
command 'listportals free' to get a list of portals that are free to use the
portal spell on (meaning they don't have a portal in them already).  Also, make
sure there isn't a portal object at the portal you are at.  If you want to use
astral, helical, etc you can use it without worring if a portal is created there
or not.

Once you decide to use a spell to go to a portal, to goto that portal, all you do
is use the number next to it in listportals.  So if you want to go to [2] on the
list you would use this syntax

c 'astral' 2   or   c 'portal' 2

That is about all there is for portals.  You will have to go to the main portal in
the city to hunt for new ones, and go out and mark them for use later.  You should
look around areas for portals and it will make it easier to get to them without
walking a lot in the map.
~

1 POSITIONS~
