Qmob is used to add mobs to the quest system.  To quickly allow the addition
of new mobs, most of the stats are generated by the difficulty of the quest so
only some basics are nedded.  It, however, does allow for a lot of variety because
of the flags you can set on a mob to add anyting from extra hp to defense flags.

Only thing to really know about is the boss values.  0 is for a regular mob.  This
is the "easiest" of all mobs in the quests.  1 is for the captain mobs.  The captain
mob ranges from 1-5 mobs in the area.  These mobs always drop eq if they are humanoid
and have a good chance of loading quest eq.  The boss mob also loads eq and has the
highest chance to load quest eq.  There is only 1 boss mob per quest.

There are two flags arguments.  flags replaces all flags on the qmob and aflags toggles
any flags provided (so it will remove a flag if it exists)

NOTE:  You can set more than one flag at at time.  You set them via the number that
is available in (HELP QMOBFLAGS)
