2 QUEST5~
#General~
#END~
quest view [quest num]
quest static <difficulty> <vnums> <mob count> <area name> <filename> <reset time>

All commands listed here are imm only.  Quest view allows you to view what quests
are currently running and who is involved.  You can type the command without the
quest view option to get a short list of all quests.  Providing the number will
give a detailed view of the quest.

Quest static creates a static area that can be linked into the game.  This will
create a self-sustained area with all mobs/objects saved in the area and resets
will be generated for the area.  This area will save all equipment including
stuff created on the ground and in inventories.  All forge equipment will be
copied to the area and will behave like normal forge equipment.  Once the area
is done, there will be no changes to the area (hence the static option).

Once you have decided the static area is perfect for you, you can use the command 
foldqarea (HELP FOLDQAREA) to fold the area and install it into the game. If you choose 
not to use the area, you can use the command unloadqarea (HELP UNLOADQAREA) to take the 
area out and try again. Once unloadqarea is used, you can use the exact filename and area 
name that you used before. The options for static areas are difficulty (1-13), vnums 
(50-2000), mob count(20 to 500), area name (put in quotes for more than 1 word), 
filename, and then reset time (1 to 10080). Note: Mob count is a percentage. 20 percent 
of a 100 vnum area = 20 mobs (plus bosses/captains). 

Note:  Vnums for static areas are 200,000 - 299,999.  Vnums for an area are taken
after the highest vnum in this range.  So if there is a massive gap between the
areas you will lose the amount of static areas you can have.  It is best to do 1
static area at at time.  Do it offline, keep loading them till you find the 1
you want, foldqarea then move on.
~

1 QUICKCOMBO~
#General~
