-1 RAFERMAND~
#General~
#END~
Rafermand is the name of the World in which we play in.  It is also the name of
the Central Continent in Rafermand (confused yet).  Rafermand was orginally thought
up by Xerves and created in August of 1998 in the form of an RoT mud.  This lasted
about 2 or 3 months until November of 1998 in which it was setup as a Smaug mud (hence
the birthdate of Rafermand in November).  Then around February or so, we moved to the
stormbringer server where we have been since.  The code featured then can be explained
best as pre Fear 1.0.  I was just a beginning coder and was trying to get my feet wet.
During this time I published what is probably one of my two most popular snippets, the
Remort snippet, and was one of the few Smaug muds with such a system.  I also put out
the furniture snippet out at this time, which might be the most popular, I am not sure.

Later on, the release of Fear 1.0 came out, this was the time of the new Wilderness.  Afer
working with an older Wilderness with 2000 rooms, we went to the snippet released by
Samson.  After a lot of changes to the appearance and a few bug fixes (not sure if I caused
em or not) it was ready to go.  Took some time to clean it up to fix some bugs, but eventually
it was up and running.  This was the time of the skill system changes, Wilderness changes,
and the beginning of two companies, the Chocobos (and their past) and the Highwaymen.

Next came Fear 1.1 which added more changed (more skill changes) and some other big changes.
The game play was still fairly similar, but we are building up to 2.0

Then we arrive on Beta 2.0.  2.0 is a huge step away from what 1.x was and a big change on
the playing system that a few didn't like (and a pwipe).  Most of the default Smaug systems
were rewritten and new systems like forge, battle, no level/classes, balanced skill system,
and other things were introduced.  2.0 is oriented toward kingdom related warfare and peaceful
actions, just depending on what the players wanted.

Would like to think all those who have contributed over the past 3 years and hopefully to the
next 3...
~

