3 RESETS~
#Immortal Building Resets~
#END~
When it comes to making sure everything works ok, there are a few things
to consider when planning resets.  Here are a few things you should know
about resets, and changes to the reset system in FeAr Code.

1.  Mobs now reset based on a serial number given to them when they are loaded
    into the world.  You do not set this serial in anyway, so just don't worry about
    it.
2.  Because of the serial resets, mobs load as they are added.  You cannot expect to put
    in one reset for a mob and have a count of 4 of them in the old system.  If one mobile is
    added into the reset list, one is added.
3.  Never use instazone, even if it is available.
4.  instaroom works very well for adding resets in a room.  It will correctly pick up any reset
    and do proper nesting of objects in objects, etc.
5.  If you want to do an instazone, it is recommended that you do a rat <begin vnum> <end vnum>
    instaroom.  This will reset all the rooms in an area.
6.  You can use the reset command to manually add resets, edit resets, shift resets, or delete them
7.  If you do manual resets, remember that you need to have any objects on a mob or in an item to follow
    the reset for that mobile or object.
8.  reset edit is good for changing a room of a mobile if you need to spread them out.  This will keep
    any equiped items on the mobile properly reset too. 
9.  Time based resets have a few tricky rules, might check out (HELP TIMERESETS) for more info

&w&CSEE ALSO:  &w&WRESET   RESETCMDS   INSTAROOM   TIMERESETS
~

