A very powerful spell used to resurrect the dead corpse of an ally.  You must
be physically in the room with the corpse of the target and the target must
be online (including not writing notes, etc).  Once the spell is casted on
the corpse the target will receive a message along with the rez percent.  The
percent is the amount of lost con is returned along with the percentage of
hp/mana/move that is restored upon accepting.

The actual command used to accept a rez is resurrection.  Just typing the command
without any arguments shows you the percent you have now.  Typing the yes argument
will accept the rez.

While this is a great spell, there are a few things to be aware of

1.  resurrection has a time limit, which is roughtly 1-3 hours depending on
    the strength of the spell.  After the time limit you cannot rez a corpse.
2.  resurrection will not resurrection an equipment less corpse due to the
    fact it's timer gets reset down to about 5 minutes.  If you catch it just
    as the target dies you might be able to get it of though....
3.  You can only resurrect a corpse once.  Once this is done the corpse is
    marked as resurrected and the target's lost con value is reset so unless
    the target dies another resurrection cannot occur.  So make sure you
    are accepting a rez for the right corpse.
4.  If you died 40 times and lost 3 con points, you can only recover a max
    of 1 con point.
5.  There is a rez affect that lasts 1 minute that lowers your hp/mana regen
    rate and decreases your armor and tohit value.
6.  A rez is removed if the player logs off.  The con loss is however kept over
    no matter if a corpse is lost or not.
~

