1 ROOF~
#Kingdoms Creation~
#END~
Syntax: roof build
Syntax: roof update
Syntax: roof destroy

Roof is used to create a roof around your building so the outside cannot
see in and the inside cannot see out.  This feature is new in 2.1 and offers
a lot of interesting uses.  In the new system, your building options are cut
down quite a bit from the old system, but the ability to create closed off
rooms is something altogether new and very interesting.  Once a roof is placed
on a room, a door can control rather you can see inside/outside of the room.
If the door is closed, you cannot see inside and the people inside cannot see
the outside world.  This can be very useful if you want to keep people out
of your business while you are inside of your town.  In order to use this
command, you first need to understand the whole idea on how to create a room.

2 sectortypes are involved in this creation, inside and wall.  In order to use
either one, you need to have first did a makeroom (help MAKEROOM).  Once the
rooms you want to use are in place, you can then create a roof over the rooms.
In order to do this, all the inside sectors have to have either an inside
sector in all directions or a wall.  If any other sector is discovered, the
area is not "closed off" so a roof cannot be built.  Here are two examples of
a closed off area and one that is not.

IIIII
I%%%D
IIIII

In the above example, I is the wall, % is the inside sector, and D is the door.
As you can see, there is no gap in the example.  Now here is an example that
will not work
IIIIII
I%%%%%D
IIIIIII

As you notice, ne of the last % there is an open space.  A roof will not be built
in this example.

Lastly, you can only have 100 doors per town, so choose them wisely.
~

