1 SCHEDULE~
#General~
#END~
Syntax: schedule view <town>
Syntax: schedule add <town> <start period> <end period> <resource> [reoccur]
Syntax: schedule remove <town> <number>

Schedule is used to place workers out during a certain period of the year.  It
will automate the training and the extraction of these workers for you.  I will
repeat this only once though, the system is not foolproof and should in no way
be ran over a long period of time unmanaged.  You never know when someone sneaks
up and kills your worker and then you are out a worker plus whatever the worker
was working on.  The system will not respawn any workers for you if they die.  With
that....

Schedule can be used by the mayor of a town to schedule workers for that town
or can be used by King/number1/number2 to manage any town.  You use view to check out
the schedule for that town, add to add something, and remove to well remove.  The only
really tricky thing is the period value.  Workers now work on a 7.5 GD (4.5 RL Hour)
system, so you can place them on this schedule in a period on it.  There are 48 periods
(48 * 7.5 = 360 = 1 GY).  Anyway, below is a chart with the time of the periods to make
it easier on you.

