1 SHEATH DRAW DRAWING SHEATHING~
#Combat~
#END~
Syntax: sheath
Syntax: draw [target]

New to Rafermand as of this helpfile is sheathing code.  You might of
seen it elsewhere in other muds, but it allows you to put a weapon in
a sheath and pull it out and wield it upon demand.  The "draw" command
allows you to draw a weapon from the sheath and wield and and the
"sheath" command allows you to withdraw the weapon from combat and
put it in your sheath.  Here are a few rules and pointers on how the
code works.

1.  Sheath must be worn to work, it goes on the waist and typically layes
    over the waist item.
2.  It is possible to wear 2 sheaths and a waist item.  You just need to
    play around with them to learn how to wear all 3.
3.  When you draw, you automatically draw to the wield position if you have
    dual wield.  So if you draw twice, make sure to have your primary weapon 
    in your first sheath.
4.  When you sheath, you will first sheath your dual wield weapon if you have
    one.
5.  Each sheath can only hold ONE weapon of a certain type and has a max weight
    limit on that weapon.  You can learn both of these values by examining it.
6.  Sheath's can break like containers, so repair them if needed.
7.  You can target a mob when you draw, just put in the name of the mob.  It will
    draw your weapon and attack.  Will not work on players yet though.
~

3 SHEATHRULES~
#Immortal Building BuildingObjs~
#END~
When making sheaths there are a few rules to go by to keep the world
in balance and make sure it doesn't cause problems with the code.
Here is what you need to keep in mind.

1.  Each item needs to be layered properly.  If it is a back item, it
    cannot be layered and should not.  As for the waist item, here is
    the layer values and what they can have/cannot have

layer 1 - Waist item, treat it as a normal item, can have affects.
layer 2 - Sheath, normal sheaths, no affects and no nogive flags.
layer 4 - Special Sheaths, little affects and nogive flag.

    It is possible to have a normal sheath on layer 4, it is not a good
    idea to have a special on on layer 2.  Also, layer 1 needs to be
    reserved for waist items only, so don't use that layer.  This works
    so that the lowest layer goes on first and then you put on layer 2
    and then layer 4.

2.  Wear locations have to be either back or waist.  Back doesn't have layers

3.  Unless it is layer 4, no affects.  If it is a layer 4, try to keep it to
    minimal affects, such as 10HP 1 str, very little or none.  If it isn't on
    a level 40 or higher mob, it shouldn't have affects.  Ask someone in the
    building council for more details on what is acceptable

4.  If a sheath has a nogive flag, it only accepts weapons with nogive flags to
    put into it.  It automatically searches for a sheath with a nogive flag if a
    weapon with a nogive flag on it is used during the sheath command.

5.  The sn value is used only if drawn during battle.  As of this helpfile writing,
    this value is not in use though, just provide it for future use.  Also, the sn
    can only be an attack spell, if it is found to be elsewise, someone will get
    screamed at very badly.

6.  If you provide a vnum for V2, only that weapon can be put into that sheath for it
    was made only for that weapon and any other one will not work.  These types of
    sheaths SHOULD NOT be made by anyone without consent of the building council or
    on occasion on a quest.  These types of sheaths usually have bonus affects because
    they are better and are the most rare kind of sheaths.

7.  If you leave the percent at 0, it defaults to a 25 percent chance.  Also, you are not
    to create a sheath with a spell on it without first asking.
~

