1 SHIELDS~
#Combat~
#END~
Shields are a common item in most muds.  However, in Rafermand we have changed
shields to play a slightly different role, one which you see in some games, and
in some you don't.

A shield comes in two varities, the 1-handed version and the 2-handed version.
The pavis (the one you can create) is the 2-handed version.  When one uses a
pavis they get the excellent durability and block percent of the shield, but
they cannot use any weapons while in battle, nor cast any spells, quaff potions,
brandish a staff, etc.  This is mostly useful for avoiding projectiles over a large
range.  One might think it is useful for tanking (taking all the damage in a fight),
but mobs are smarter than that and will start to attack a new target if they are
having problems with your shield.

The one-handed vareity come in different sizes.  From small bucklers to massive size
tower shields.  As one would expect, bucklers are harder to block with and break easier,
but they have their advantages.  Large shields take up something called lag time.  Just
like weapons have a certain lag time between battle, shields do too.  The larger the
shield, the more lag time.  So it is important to consider which shield is correct for
the situation.  On a final note, you cannot use two-handed weapons with shields.

Lastly, there is also a skilled call shieldblock in the Warrior sphere.  You can
increase your percent to block with all shields by increasing your skill in it.

Note:  Wearing a shield will make a mob less aggressive toward you.  This can be good or
bad depending on what you are looking for.

