get a new refresh of the picture to show up if it is deleted.  Also, sometimes that file
is not there and you cannot see the picture and you need to shutdown zmud and run it
again.  So the main words of wisdom, get the URL right the first time or you will be
having players asking how to fix it.

Lastly, an image can be pushed to a player or simply available online and then stored
in the Image Folder, then the picture can be pulled up at anytime for use.  Also, it
is best to stick to .gif and .jpg, not sure what else is supported (.jpeg will not work
