1 'SKILL POINTS' 'SKILL POINT' SPOINTS SPOINT~
#General~
#END~
Skill points are gained randomly after a successful battle.  They will
be gained most of the time, but not all the time.  You will gain more
points from defeating harder enemies (so you cannot just sit around and
smack down the easiest mobs in the game for a ton of points).  Once
you get enough points you can either increase your skills/spells by 1
star or a whole point (HELP TALENT) to learn more about the talent skill
used for that reason.

Since Rafermand is trying to encourage grouping, a new system has been
deviced for sharing skill points during a battle.  It is based on the
value you see in your score called your SWorth (HELP SWORTH).  You receive
a cut of the skill points in a group based on that.  For more rules reguarding
group cuts and rates check out the SWORTH helpfile.

Lastly, as you advance into Tier 2-4 skills/spells (HELP TIER) you will find
that the cost will go up.  It won't be a large increase, but an extra hurdle
standing in your way of advancement.
~

1 SKILLADVANCEMENT~
#General~
#END~
Our skill system offers two ways to advance a skill/spell.  You can either
just use it (rather in battle or not in battle depending on the type of
skill/spell) or you can use skill points toward advancing it.  Skill
points are gained after a successful win.  For more information over
Skill points see (HELP SKILL POINTS).  Once you earn enough of these
points you can use the command talent (HELP TALENT) to spend your points
on advancing one star or a whole point in any skill/spell that you
have available.  There are quite a few rules reguarding skill points
and groups, so please check the helpfile there for the rules.

Once you gain enough points you can eventually increase mastery and move
on to higher tiers (HELP MASTERY and HELP TIERS).
