1 SKILLGROUP SKILLGROUPS 'SKILL GROUP' 'SKILL GROUPS' 'MAGIC GROUP' 'MAGIC GROUPS'~
#General~
#END~
A skillgroup (sometimes called a group or a skill group or a spell group)
Is part of the hierachy of the skill system.  The hierarchy looks like this

   Sphere->SkillGroup->(Skill/Spell)

A skillgroup is actually what contains all the skills and spells and affects
how you can advance up in Tiers (HELP TIER).  Once you gained so many skills
to a certain requirement (again HELP TIER) you then are able to obtain
the next Tier of skills or spells.  This makes it possible to have Tier 4 in
one group an only Tier 2 in another group.  

SEE ALSO:  learn listgroups skillrules mastery tiers spheres skillscommand sbook forget
           skilladvancement
~

1 SKILLPOINT SKILLPOINTS SPELLPOINT SPELLPOINTS 'SKILL POINT' 'SKILL POINTS' 'SPELL POINT' 'SPELL POINTS'~
#General~
#END~
Each skill or spell has a point value.  You start at 1 and can go up
as far as 20.  As you increase the points (through use or the talent
command (HELP TALENT HELP SPOINTS)) you gain more power in that skill
or spell.  There is also mastery (HELP MASTERY) that affects the strength
of that skill/spell.  If you do not increase the mastery as soon as you
can (4 points for novice, 7 for expert, etc) you will find it harder to
gain points.  So, it is important to advance your mastery as soon as you
can.

~

1 SKILLREQUIREMENTS~
#General Skills~
#END~
In order to learn certain skills/spells in a group, you must first follow
a certain method to learn them.  Every group (well almost every group) will
require so many skills to be at a certain mastery before you can start learning
new skills.  This is how it works.

Skills are broke down into their mastery types.  When you type listgroups Fire
you will get a list of all the spells in Fire.  The Yellow are Beginner types, the
Cyan are Novice types, etc.  In order to start learning Novice type skills, you need
so many Beginner type skills at Novice.  To see how many you need, you can try to learn
a Novice type skill, or type listgroups toadvance <group>.  This will tell you how many
you need to learn the next mastery type.  It works the same with Expert, you will need
so many Novice types at Expert.

Once you reach this requirement, you can then start to learn Novice type skills by
learning it from Beginner on.
~

1 SKILLRULES SKILLCOST MASTERYCOST~
#General Skills~
#END~
It is important to know a few things about the system, here are those
things.

 - It takes 0 points and 500 gold to get to Beginner
 - It takes 4 points and 3000 gold to get to Novice
 - It takes 7 points and 20000 gold to get to Expert
 - It takes 10 points and 100000 gold to get to Master
 - It takes 14 points and 500000 gold to get Elite
 - It takes 17 points and 2000000 gold to get Flawless
 - Spell groups require books to learn the spells
 
In addition to all of this, there can be extra cost if you are using a kingdom
trainer.  Kingdoms are allowed to tax the usage of their trainers, so it might
cost a bit more to use their trainer, or ungodly amounts more depending on the
value of the trainer.  In addition, there are additional requirements that are
listed in the learn helpfile (HELP LEARN).  It is a good idea to have read that
helpfile too.  Then there is the spheres helpfile (HELP SPHERES), again a good
read.

&w&CSEE ALSO:  &w&WLEARN    SKILLS    TIERS    SPHERES
~

1 SKILLS SPELLS~
#Skills~
#END~
If you are looking for information over the skills command use (HELP SKILLSCOMMAND)
This is the main helpfile over the skill system of Rafermand.  This is one of the more
complex skills system available and it is also one of the most unique systems.  We offer
a sphere based system where you can learn skills/spells from 5 different spheres: Warrior,
Thief, Hand-to-Hand, Mage, Cleric.  Since we do not offer classes, you have the potential
to learn anything you want.  You can mix in a little bit of Thief into your Mage, or Mage
into your Thief, etc.  However, we have a counter-balancing system that makes it harder and
harder to learn things that are not in the same sphere.  So you can have a mage-thief, but
it will be harder to advance in skills/spells then with just a mage.  It gets even harder
if you have mage-cleric-thief.

For more information on how to actually advance in a skill, please check out the helpfile
(HELP SKILLADVANCEMENT).  This has changed recently offering two methods of advancement, via
talent command and by actual use.

This system is fairly complex and there are helpfiles listed
below that explain every aspect of this system.  It is HIGHLY recommended that you read them.

NOTE:  A new restriction has been added, HELP MASTERY RESTRICTIONS for more info.

&w&CSEE ALSO:  &w&Wlearn listgroups skillrules mastery tiers spheres skillscommand sbook forget
           skilladvancement skillgroup masterycost
~

