1 STABLE STABLES~
#Wilderness Mounts~
#END~
Stables are special tracks of land you can buy on the Wilderness for
placing a Stable.  In order to place a stable, you need to go to the
local caste official in your town (in Rafermand that is w of recall)
and buy a S class license.  Once you do so, you can go out to the
Wilderness and use the command makestable to place a stable.  The
rules for building one is that you have to stand in a room next to
the room you want to have the stable in, and type makestable dir.
Also, the stable has to be created in plains, hills, or fields.  Once
you have created the stable, you can use the stable command to use the
stable.

The stable command has 5 options you can use
      build store list retrieve release

build    - Add 3 more slots for mounts (you get 3 initially).  You need a
           S Additional License to do this (get from caste guy).
store    - Can place your mount in the stables (has to be a saveable mount)
list     - List the current mounts in the stables
retrieve - Retrieve the mount from the stable (uses the number from list)
release  - Release your current mount into the Wilderness.

As of now, that is all that is available.  Later there will be options to
add to allow traiding so you can let people come in and take one of yours
in trade for money (which will become a job later on).
Just remember, making stables only work if you are in the Wilderness and
have the S Class License.

 Note: The direction you type when you create the stable is where the link on
the Wilderness will be, in the actual stable, the link back out will be opposite
of that direction.  So if you type makestable e, the entrance will be to the
east and the exit to the west.

