Since rafermand is a levelless mud (HELP LEVELS) we feature different ways to increase and
decrease stats (hp, str, int, etc).  Each stat in itself is important in certain areas and
you might want to only focus on a few stats because you might not really need some of the
others.  Each stat has its own helpfile, which is listed below, but each stat works somewhat
like this.

Each time you use a trigger effect (something that increases or decreases a stat) it either
loses or gains a few points.  Once it reaches the max, it goes up one point, or when it goes
to 0, it decreases a point.  Each stat is different in how this happens and how fast, but
all of them do this.  To see the status of a stat you might be working on, you can type
(gscore) (HELP GSCORE).  It will give you an idea on how well you are doing on increasing
a stat.  It will be up to you to figure out the best way to increase your stats, and figure
out the limits you have on how much you can increase it and HOW FAST.  Some stats will only
let you go so fast on it before it starts to remove points.  This is discussed in each helpfile
for the stat, so start reading below.

