1 TIER TIERS TIER1 TIER2 TIER3 TIER4~
#Skills~
#END~
In the magic/skill system there are sets of spells and skills that fall into something called
a tier.  There are 4 tiers: Tier 1 Tier 2 Tier 3 Tier 4.  The first tier is the weakest of the 4
tears with Tier 4 being the strongest.  In order to advance up to the next Tier, you will need so
many of the previous Tier to a certain mastery: x amount of Tier 1 at Novice, x amount of Tier 2
at Expert, x amount of Tier 3 at Master (HELP MASTERY).  In order to find the x in this value, you
need to use listgroups toadvance <group> (HELP LISTGROUPS).  Once you complete your requirement for
the next tier, you can learn any spell/skill in that group's Tier.  If you even fall out of this
requirement, you will not be able to learn *ANY NEW* skills/spells in that Tier.  However, you can
still advance in the ones that you have started to learn.  A lot of times it is important to get rid
of lower Tier spells/skills that are useless but only to advance in Tier.  You can do this by not
using it, and in time it will disappear.

It is important to remember that a Tier 3 spell at Beginner might be better than a Tier 1 spell
at Expert or even Master, so just because you have a high mastery rating in a spell/skill doesn't
make it better than a higher Tier spell/skill.  It is important to find a group or two you like and
try to climb the Tiers as quickly as possible to get to the Tier 3 spells, and perhaps the Tier 4
spell if you element allows it (HELP ELEMENTS).

To see what tier a spell or skill is in, all you need to do is use listgroups <group>.  This will show
you a listing of every spell and skill in a certain group.  You should notice some colors with each
spell/skill.  &c&YYELLOW is Tier1  &cDark Cyan is Tier2  &CBright Cyan/Blue is Tier3  &RRed is Tier4

&CSEE ALSO:  &G&WMASTERY    LISTGROUPS    SKILLS    ELEMENTS    MAGIC
~

