3 TIMERESETS~
#Immortal Building Resets~
#END~
In order to add a timereset to a mobile or object, you need to use the
reset time command.  Its syntax is as followed.

Syntax:  reset time <number> <time to reset>  --in seconds
Syntax:  reset time left <number>             --Shows Time Left till Reset
Syntax:  reset time forcereset <number>       --Sets the time to reset to now, will reset next reset area tick

It is important to remember a few rules when adding time based resets.

1.  Setting TTR (time to reset) to 0 removes the time reset function from a reset.
2.  Setting TTR to -1 makes it load only once.
3.  Setting TTR > 0 sets it to a time based reset.
4.  Resets do not load as soon as the TTR triggers.  It is reset every time the next
    reset area tick comes by.  So if you have a lot of time based resets, you might set
    and area's reset ticks to 1 minute.
5.  Time based resets do not actually go into affect till the mob/object is loaded by the
    reset code.  So in short, if the mob/obj is loaded once you set the resets, you need to
    purge the mobs/objs to make sure the time based reset is in action.
6.  Time based resets are triggered by 3 actions for objs and 1 for mobs.  The 3 actions for objs
    are obj_from_obj, obj_from_char, obj_from_room.  This means if an item is disarmed, stollen, junked
    destroyed, loaded to a corpse, or moved in any fashion, it is triggered.  Mobs are triggered by
    extract_char.  This is called anytime a mob is killed or removed from the game (purge)
7.  Time based resets of -1 are removed from the reset list once they are triggered.  If you don't want
    this to happen, set the time to something like 300mil seconds (10 years) so you can choose to reinstate
    it later.

&w&CSEE ALSO:  &c&WRESETS   RESET   INSTAROOM
~

