1 TOWN TOWNS~
#Kingdoms~
#END~
Towns are the main units of the kingdom.  There are two levels of a kingdom,
the kingdom wide settings and the town settings.  The kingdom has a default
town that some taxes are pumped into from across the kingdom.  This default
town is setup by default as the first town you create using startkingdom.
You can, however, change this using the townvalues command.  

Towns can be controlled by two factions, the mayor of the town, and those
who have the ranking in the kingdom to control towns no matter of who
controls them.  Just like in kingdoms, there are certain values and permissions
you can grant with a town, these are done with the townvalues command
(HELP TOWNVALUES).

Lastly, towns now each can control their own units.  The barracks have been
moved from the kingdom and into each town.  These units can be controlled
by the town owners or those who have command of troops.  Units can be
purchased by using coins earned from taxes from a kingdom (HELP TOWNSIZE) for
more information over things like units and moral.

If you are looking to start a town, talk to your King and ask for a Mayor's License
so you can get started on your new town.  The cost of a new town are as such.

80000 gold coins
30000 units of Lumber
20000 units of Stone

In order to create a new town, you need to have the permission from a town in
the kingdom to expand from.  They first need to set their expansion permissions
on and then you need to be connected to the town via a road.  If either one of
these is not ready, you will not be able to start a new town.  Once this is done,
the resources will be removed from the town you are expanding from, and depending
on the size, the town might decrease in size.  If the Expansions value in townvalues
is 0, the town will decrease, otherwise, the town will stay the same size.  It is
best to expand from larger cities because they can be expanded from without a loss.
~

