1 TOWNSIZE~
#Kingdoms~
#END~
Town Size is a very important figure in town management.  In the old system there
use to be a number of civilians in each town, now there is just a single town size.
The town size affects things such as the number of units you can have (HELP UNITS),
the AOC (HELP AOC), the number of units you can have training (HELP TRAINING), the
amount of resources needed to increase moral (HELP MORAL), the different kinds of
units you can purchase along with the speed of training for that unit, and lastly
how many rooms you can build in your town (HELP BUILD HELP MAKEROOM).  To make things
short, here is a small table.

SIZE    NAME             CORN/WHEAT  WOOD    STONE   Coins   Units   TUnits  MUnits  Rooms 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1       camp             3000        0       0       0       1       1       -       5       
2       settlement       6000        800     0       0       2       1       -       10      
3       village          10000       1500    0       0       4       1       -       15      
4       motte bailey     15000       2500    1000    0       5       2       3       25 
5       tower            22000       4000    1500    2000    7       2       4       40      
6       stone keep       40000       6000    2500    7000    8       2       5       55     
7       small castle     70000       11000   4000    15000   10      3       6       70     
8       medium castle    110000      18000   6000    35000   12      3       7       95      
9       large castle     150000      30000   10000   80000   14      3       8       120     
10      grand castle     250000      60000   15000   150000  20      5       11      150   

The Food/Wood/Stone/Coins are the requirements per year for Single Consumption.  More
information is available at (HELP MORAL) over this system.  Units represents the number
of mobiles units you can have, TUnits represents the number of training units you can
have at one time, and MUnits represents the maximum amount of units you can have before
moral is directly affected (HELP MORAL).  Rooms are the number of rooms you have available
to build with.  To increase your townsize, you have to increase moral and then ultimately
grow on your Growth Month (indicated by GMonth in townvalues).  Again, more of this available
in the (HELP MORAL) helpfile.
~

