1 TWINK~
#General~
#END~
For starts, if you are unfamiliar with the word Twink, here is a brief description. It is
MUD jargon for a person that steps outside of his/her RP bounds to show his/her superpowers.
In a more PKill oriented game it simply means a person who likes to kill individuals much
weaker than he/she. Lastly, if you googled the word twink you will probably notice some
links to gay porn sites. It also is word uses in the gay culture, which probably was used
as a rather nasty insult by some 15 year old to another *laugh*.

Twink killing is the art of killing people who are weaker than you. Typically it is in
regard to killing newbies just because you can. This does not create a very healthy
learning experience for newbies so the game will not allow it. However, there are different
situations where you can kill someone who is weaker than you.

1. You are challenged to a duel. There are no checks here.
2. The person you are attacking has a cloak on and is hooded. A person that is hidden like
   such is treated as an equal in this check (but not in Power Ranking)
3. If the person is involved in a kingdom that is at war with your kingdom. There are no
   rules here due to the nature of being in a kingdom that is suppose to be protecting and
   arming you.
4. You are in an arena. These areas are a free for all and will not count.

Twink killing will be defined by killing anyone that is more than 5 Power Levels below your
own. You will know this value unless the person is cloaked so it is not like you will not
know. Once the twink killing is committed, twink points will be assigned to your characters
depending on the nastiness of the death (anywhere from 5-25 points). If you collect 100
points your character will be reset. You have the right to contest a twink point add, but
you take the risk of the immortal adding more twink points if you are trying to cheat the
system (or even worse).

On a final note, the twink check is started at the beginning of a battle and will be assigned
based on that value. This value will be reset anytime a fight is broken up (flee, etc). This
prevents some cheating of the system by removing all of ones equipment before death to stack
on a stiff penalty.
~

