1 WEAPONSIZEMORT~
#General~
#END~
First off, weaponsize and weight are two different things.  Weight of
a weapon does affect how well you can wield it, but it doesn't affect
your combat speed.  Weaponsize is a value given to a weapon based on
the actual size of a weapon and what race it is.  An Ogre Long Sword
is going to have more weaponsize than a Hobbit Long Sword.  Each race
has a certain section of weaponsize that they can wield.  If you are
at the bottom of that limit you will swing the weapon very very quickly.
If you are at the top of that limit you will swing the weapon much
slower.

It is important to take this into consideration.  Sometimes using a weapon
that wasn't meant for your race can come in handy due to weaponsize.
~

2 WEAPONSYS~
#Immortal Building BuildingObjs~
#END~
The weaponsystem really hasn't changed that much in 2.0.  You have the
weaponsizes (HELP WEAPONSIZE).  Mainly, the heavier the weapon, the more
time it is going to take to attack (half a second per one).  This time can
be improved by wearing lighter armor, spells, and agility.

Each race also gets a increase/decrease modifier on gaining agility.  It goes
as follows.

Fairy    140%
Hobbit   120%
Elf      105%
Human    100%
Dwarf     85%
Ogre      70%

&G&WSEE ALSO:  &CWEAPONSIZE
~

