1 WEATHERINFO~
#General~
#END~
Our weather system is unique in the realm of mudding because it is not 
based off what most new weather systems are, the Medevia Weather System. 
Our system is based off of moving weather systems called currents. These 
currents move a certain direction (cold fronts move se and warm fronts move 
sw, cold fronts start nw and warm fronts ne) and bring along them change in 
weather, precipitation, and winds. As the weather changes, so does the 
precipitation, it comes in the way of either rain, snow, or ice. Of course 
each is based off of the temperature of the area, so you will only be 
seeing snow in the colder areas of the weather, not in the middle of 
summer. Also, the temperature is warmest at the center of the world, and 
grows colder as it branches out to the north and south side. 

In addition to precipitation, when two fronts hit eachother, there is a 
chance that a Tornado will occur (there is also a temperature variable). 
Tornados are very dangerous, in particular in the Caste map because it can 
disrupt sectors and throw your loyal followers away from their location. 
However, in the game map, it will only throw individuals who get close 
enough to the Tornado. 

That is mainly it, the system offers the basic weather design, and will be 
a lot more valuable later on when new skills/spells are offered that are 
more weather designed and use the power of the weather to reak havoc. 

Lastly, it is important to be properly equiped when going outside of the 
cities. If it is really cold, if you are not properly equiped, you will 
suffer damage, and if you stay out too long, you will die. In the warm 
weather, if you are not wearing shoes, you will also suffer damage, so be 
equiped (this is primarily for Wilderness, and some areas). In addition, if 
you think the 15 second update on the weather is too spammy, you can change 
it by turning on the noweather config option in CONFIG. Also, you can add 
similar values to your prompt with %w and %W (help wprompt for more info). 
~

1 WEB SNARE STEPBACK~
#General~
#END~
Syntax:  c 'web' [target]
Syntax:  c 'snare' [target]
Syntax:  stepback

A very powerful spell added to the Wizardry sphere that allows mages to
stop an opponents in their tracks.  Once the target is stopped you can
either continue fighting or use the stepback command to get out of combat.
If all mobs you are fighting are webbed combat will end and you will have
a chance to either flee or continue combat in another manner.  If you wish
to use magic or projectiles you have a good chance of landing an attack and
not getting attacked back.

When an enemy is webbed that enemy cannot attack back if you have stepped out
of battle (note, you have to step out of battle or it will keep pounding on
you).  Once out of battle every 4 seconds there is a chance the creature will
break the web (based on strength and intelligence).  Also, the web can be broken
if damage is done to the enemy.  If it is in the form of magic or a projectile the
changes are greater.  If a fire spell is used the chance is the greatest.

As for snare, it is the same as web but the duration is longer, the chance of
landing is better, and breaking it is much more difficult.  The only downside is
it is a Tier 4 spell so only those who wish to stay dominantly wizard will ever
get to use it.

Lastly, stepback can be used if the target is stunned (either through a stun or
if their hp is < 0).  Anytime you choose to run away instead of fight and the
mob is aggressive, it will give chase after the web is broken.  However, web has
a longer life than a stun so you might be long gone before the poor thing even
has a chance.
~

1 WEIGHT~
#Combat~
#END~
The weight of a weapon affects how well you can wield it.  Depending on
your strength, you can wield a weapon without any reduction in speed
besides the normal weaponsize reductions.  However, if you go over your
max weight, you will see this message in Red.

Wielding such a heavy weapon is going to slow you down!!

This means you have gone over your max allowed weight.  For every 3 you
go over, it will take 1 second longer in combat.  The max combat lag is
12 seconds.
~

