1 WORKERUNIT~
#Kingdoms~
#Kingdoms Military~
#END~
A worker unit is used to extract resources from the game.  A worker unit can be placed
at two locations: in your AOC or at a storage bin.  If placed in your AOC, the worker
will go out and look for resources to extract and then dump the resources back into
your town.  If using a storage bin, the unit will dump into the storage bin and then
your kingdom will need to haul the bin back.  It is much more efficient to have the
unit dump back into your town, so think about that when placing a town and planting
resources around you for extraction.

Lastly, a Worker can extract any resource, but only 1 at a time.  When you place the
mob, you tell it what resource to extract.  Once it runs out of resources to extract,
the unit will cease extracting and you won't have to pay it anymore.  Otherwise, it
will keep going and keep charging (by the RL hour).  You can get rid of a unit by
using the dismissunit command or killing it.
~

